Privacy Policy

​

The foreword.

This Privacy Policy (hereinafter the “Policy”) is intended to help you to ascertain how do we collect your information (or "data"), why do we collect that information, with whom do we share your information and how long do we store it. Additionally, here you can find the information on how can you manage the processing of your information and what rights do you have in the course of the processing of your information by us.

What information about you do we collect?

When you use our Application, we collect the following information about you:

Device data. We collect the following information about your device:

The version of Android and its firmware (build);

The information about the model of your device, its manufacturer;

The information about your Device ID and other related identifiers;

The language and time-zone, chosen on your device;

The information about your device display (screen size and resolution);

The information from the accelerometer, pedometer, vibration accelerometer of your device (if applicable);

The information on Google accounts, installed on your device;

Information from your device camera (if applicable).

Location and telecommunication data:

The information about your mobile network operator and/or your internet provider;

The information about your location.

Performance data:

We monitor how do you use our Application: the buttons you clicked, the pages you visited, your performance within the Application, the information on whether or not have you read a notification or message.

 

Marketing and contact data:

The referral code you used;

Your e-mail address (if you contact us via the Application interface or by e-mail).

